<br>
I cast my MR spell on myself, give pet two elemental blankets and two daggers of symbols. Buff up pet and then inch up to the edge of the cliff.<br>
<br>
I send my pet in then back up to the cliff edge.  From there, I can nuke the sirens but they are not close enough to really notice me.  Don't sit there though until pet has firm aggro on all the mobs.<br>
<br>
Pet can solo all of them.  But they are all blue to me ( or light blue) so I typically send in one nuke for each mob to get exp.<br>
<br>
If there is an enchantress, I'll send in a few nukes, just to reduce the chance of my pet getting charmed.<br>
<br>
If your pet gets charmed, he will run off, and mobs will follow him.  He will run along the cliff end.  So what I've been doing is backing off and hovering over the water a bit on the other side of the bluff until my pet loses his charm.  Once his charm is off, i'll summon him back to my side.  From there, the sirens will either walk back to their spot or come back for the pet, who will run in to attack as soon as they are in range.  <br>
<br>
I've only been hit with a couple nukes during my whole experience soloing them.  If I don't sit, the pet seems to take all the damage.<br>
<br>
I also keep my air pet spell ready in case my pet does end up dying.  I also have sow at all times in case I need to run (which I haven't yet). Oh and lev too.<br>
<br>
It is a 20min. respawn time on the sirens.  Plenty of time to med up and let peat heal, and to kill the single wyvern spawn on the end of the cliff. <br>
<br>
Nothing wanders that direction, so there are no worries about adds.<br>
<br>
I was really scared of CS and even died once trying to kill the sirens near SG (they are all green, so they are easier right!? HA!)  But now that I have a system, CS is no threat at all.  <br>
<br>
Good luck to you!<br>
